<subSubSection id="48645446D0534B3776B07E432BEA98EB" pageId="18" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D59434CC6A23AC6406321B382369321B" pageId="18" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A3168D652C829552F2AE1DFE374A33B4" pageId="18" pageNumber="37">Body piceous. Elytral surface smooth, impunctate, elytral striae complete, 4 setiferous punctures on interval 3, stria 2 absent, prominent humeral tooth at junction of third stria with marginal channel. Profemur glabrous. Abdominal sternum VII with 5+5 setiferous punctures.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EF365E4E2255D49D284D0B1FBF1366E2" pageId="18" pageNumber="37" type="habitus">
